  "prompt": "How often should one visit a dentist?",
  "response": "It is generally recommended to visit a dentist every six months for a routine check-up and cleaning. However, the frequency of dental visits can vary depending on an individual's oral health needs. Some people with a higher risk of dental problems, such as gum disease or cavities, may need to visit more frequently, while those with excellent oral health might require less frequent visits. It's best to follow the advice of your dentist, who can provide a recommendation based on your specific oral health status.",
